[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring error handling in code**\n\nI'm considering how to handle errors, especially with unsupported features, in dynamic-access calls before GroovyShell evaluation. The `eval` function seems to create a new HashMap before evaluating, which may lead to issues in Native Image. Should I catch errors from `JsonPath.get(\"user.name\")`? It's crucial to ensure assertion behavior on the JVM. If Native Image encounters an unsupported feature error due to dynamic class loading, can I catch and return it? Yes, as long as this behavior is necessary for generated bytecode after the build. Should I import NativeImageSupport? What about existing tests?", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0020177e95fb5f45016a0052021c888197b7fcf7821aade30e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqAFIPeDB36NVhQn3sH-MgOC-JMFVasgMdHOuFxZkcHrUUNffcRPXrKDO9Veir4OSbkuFtxbD-gs8YuGxO6BNpbhxaNNuNbJTGws89qdNiH_pIjon9a_yKKELAZeGLMwbrU0kHJWhJclm-UxXK6dJZYgQ5jVaarx6ErbHlimjbTXkvE49nl7NCfgMZbwwa1U5AGEhaQTEAjBXYgRNH29hAMH73z1kACL-DbV1j_tHjVFaHYheV1Yp9D21hlh8_391C9xJ_ufj1UQeYoMTyAJODzvGwa2eeSop5M8RR7-sb8R6wwAM_I7G3bi1n2ItvJ7BTpKQwHFgYEGgM-20N0WT1Oe9LIapTBZ1FPg_f7gFGprzozpy49-VTsgLA8FAaNyO8VjfCVxPJhGegr6xE4ME7A1GBSvPNgo8f1b3_eWtCIGEj1gzhuNwQcOwO6eeH781wquQj_jgmjTf_x67Z92gKlmlk8FbfHahMT7OI4wy-g8IDhtt6Uw-swodn_AukA94XTqpvVmWW99N3VQAcib5AKkgkKbLYJPyb1HuWJR9MvvaKpgW5U4Lpk1yAWUTpgvyJYlj8x92wQmk5h-ChcDUJ4t-V2ey-_aM0YGOkQver05uRNkOLgvPBKXOfAuSqn3hulmw0hE_lVhvikKtPTXA4RoTtjaXCY5i9PHjXwOxnA_y4psf1k_s-0t74n5G4YmFt6cDHagMhVJ6bJqbXCarZZceEn-8kQhq0xeG3JTCe3183qaFwR1gI8uPxtV-a29toUrghAOFerQbJjZ2iBj43Tj0zJBz5lCqvPxxPAFjqEOlDtaByyaHAag4J-dQUs29dEC2BeixUFyPp_LP8rPB5jcYB245IeUV7MGvMKL0_E9luI9QFWYoJ8yVZ4zkIKkOa4ywmdDETWmylJjVMhGremFTK9jrpCzVwaP8Fmd_J4utNGI4O5qfHDbFKtpyuueYbLPjRPNM2oCppRJS6DOUJ0baKS_KwsWwWR2MZLZiEp2i2_dIx8v4B_B1UEkWq76HtCKik5gtXgH0dgrLKw8RGUNJZBXA0-2UTkKRj8KKqPDOzTuxBBA1wv9fCKc0UNhtvNYhbFAt